}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== [ftp://ftp.aztech.com/support/malaysia/ADSL/DSL208U%20Drivers%20Installation%20Guide%20for%20Linux.pdf The USB ID for this device appears to be 1110:9031].. so the boot device (pre FW upload) would appear to be this ID incremented by one (1110:9032 if you can't count). :It is indicated in this document that this device is using [http://www.analog.com/en/obsolete/ad6486/products/product.html Eagle3 (AD6486)]. :.. it seems to present itself to the host system as an Ethernet device.
